race.comment: THANKS GORGEOUS (10) resumes from a short break. She's shown good ability in four runs to date behind some top fillies, placing behind subsequent G1 Thousand Guineas winner Ole Dancer two starts back. Drawn for every chance here and with natural improvement she'll take beating. STREET LEGAL (4) resumed with a solid run in a strongly run 1000m maiden at Pakenham when third having been close up on debut last time in. Fitter now, he should take plenty of catching. CAVERN (1) is a Brazen Beau colt on debut for the Hayes yard who looked sharp in a recent jump out win. Have to respect top yard. WINTER HAIL (6) has sown ability and can run well fresh.
